				<name type="primary" sortindex="5" value="The Wyne Tasting Game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>From the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game comes in a cloth bag and includes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) A game board, silk screened on heavy fabric &amp;#10;  2) 4 packets each with fifteen game tokens&amp;#10;  3) Instructions and rules of the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of the game is to capture five squares in a row, horizontal, vertical or diagonal!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can play with more than four people by having people play in teams sharing a marker set.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn, the player (or team) marks a square. Then, he drinks a sample of wine (as indicated on the square) or eats a sample of food (as indicated on the square). Each player starts by placing a marker on a white wine space, and from then on, he has to alternate wine and food space. You can either stay with white wine or change to blush/rose and after that to red. At a minimum, it is recommended to bring at least 3 kinds of wine, with at least one white, one blush/rose, and one red. Think of this as similar to a Pente' wine party.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are several different wines listed on the game board:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     White, Blush, and Red Wine&amp;#10;     Riesling, Pinot Noir, Chardonnay, White Zinfandel, Merlot, and &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Port&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Sweet, Dry, Fruit, and Dessert Wine&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Take as little or as much wine as you want to drink on each turn.&amp;#10;Drink responsibly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
